programme.title: Life of Pi
programme.desc: In this visually stunning adventure drama, a zookeeper's son is stranded at sea aboard a lifeboat with a zebra, an orangutan, a hyena and a Bengal tiger named Richard Parker.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: The city buzzes with anticipation over a pending execution, as Penance grapples with a moral calling at odds with Amalia's plan. With the two women at a crossroads, the Orphans must decide whom to follow.

programme.title: The Dark Knight Rises
programme.desc: The third film in the thrilling comic-book series finds Bruce Wayne donning the Batman costume once again as the Dark Knight in order to battle Catwoman and Bane, a fierce foe possessed of tremendous physical and intellectual strength.

programme.title: The Girl With All the Gifts
programme.desc: In this engaging horror thriller set in a world overrun by zombies, a trio of soldiers, a teacher and a scientist are forced to protect a young girl whose immunity to the outbreak could be the key to saving humanity.

programme.title: Betsy's Wedding
programme.desc: Alan Alda wrote, directed and stars in this tale of a financially pressed father facing his daughter's impending nuptials. Madeline Kahn, Molly Ringwald, Ally Sheedy. Stevie Dee: Anthony LaPaglia. Oscar: Joe Pesci. Eddie's Father: Joey Bishop. Jake: Dylan Walsh. Gloria: Catherine O'Hara. Georgie: Burt Young.

programme.title: City Slickers
programme.desc: Three New Yorkers sign up for a cattle drive on a western dude ranch in this comedic farce. Jack Palance won a Best Supporting Actor Oscar for his portrayal of a grizzled trail boss who leads the urban tenderfoots.

programme.title: The Hundred-Foot Journey
programme.desc: The teenage son of an Indian restaurateur finds work with his dad's culinary foe across the street in this delectable drama. With a war between the two eateries brewing, the teen merges French and Indian cuisines with delicious results.

programme.title: Employee of the Month
programme.desc: A slacker competes with a gung-ho co-worker for the chance to date their store's sexy new cashier, who has a history of dating employee-of-the-month award winners. Dane Cook and Jessica Simpson star in this winning farce. Dax Shepard, Efren Ramirez, Andy Dick, Tim Bagley. Directed by Greg Coolidge.

programme.title: 27 Dresses
programme.desc: Wedding mania gets a comic spin in the tale of Jane (Katherine Heigl), who's always a bridesmaid and never a bride. Jane's passion for all things nuptial is tested when she's asked to plan her sister's wedding to the man she secretly loves. A cynical columnist (James Marsden) who falls for Jane while surreptitiously writing a human-interest story about her further complicates Jane's dreams of love and marriage.

programme.title: Underclassman
programme.desc: Nick Cannon (\"Roll Bounce\") stars in this funny and fast-paced action comedy as a rookie bike cop who goes undercover at an elite prep school to break up a crime ring. Roselyn Sanchez, Shawn Ashmore, Angelo Spizzirri. Directed by Marcos Siega.

programme.title: Fast & Furious presents: Hobbs & Shaw
programme.desc: Officer Luke Hobbs strives to uphold justice in every facet of his life. However, when a genetically altered cyber villain begins to endanger innocent citizens, Hobbs finds that he must forge an unexpected partnership with rebel Deckard Shaw to protect those they love.

programme.title: A Black Lady Sketch Show
programme.sub-title: My Booty Look Juicy, Don't It?

programme.title: Sanctum
programme.desc: In this propulsive thriller, diver Frank McGuire (Richard Roxburgh) leads a team of underwater adventurers, including his son, into a complex series of caves, only to discover that they may be trapped when a storm cuts off their route to the surface. Produced by James Cameron.

programme.title: The Nevers
programme.desc: The city buzzes with anticipation over a pending execution, as Penance grapples with a moral calling at odds with Amalia's plan. With the two women at a crossroads, the Orphans must decide whom to follow.

programme.title: Norbit
programme.desc: Eddie Murphy is at his funniest as he plays multiple roles in this outrageous farce about a shy nerd who is married to an obese shrew, but gets a second chance to win the heart of his childhood sweetheart.

programme.title: Adventureland
programme.desc: Dejected after finding out he's no longer visiting Europe after graduating college, James takes a summer job at a small local amusement park to cover his NY grad school expenses. He falls for his co-worker Em, and together they experience love and heartbreak, and both grow over the course of the summer.

programme.title: Shallow Hal
programme.desc: In this weighty farce, superficial playboy Hal Larson (Jack Black) is only interested in attractive women until a self-help guru hypnotizes him. Then, he sees only a woman's inner beauty and promptly falls for a bighearted, 300-pound woman (Gwyneth Paltrow). Bobby and Peter Farrelly directed and wrote the script. Jason Alexander, Joe Viterelli.

programme.title: Bandits
programme.desc: Bruce Willis and Billy Bob Thornton are delightful as thieves who hold a bank manager hostage the night before a heist, then empty the vault before the start of business the next day---known as the \"Sleepover Bandits.\" Barry Levinson directed the sly comedy-drama. Cate Blanchett, Troy Garity.

programme.title: One More Time
programme.desc: In this touching drama, a musician reeling from personal and professional disappointments moves into the Hamptons home of her father, a Sinatra-esque crooner still hoping to make a career comeback. In time, father and daughter bond while seeking success in the music industry.

programme.title: The Mummy
programme.desc: Brendan Fraser is a raider of the lost sarcophagus in this rousing, high-tech remake of the 1932 horror classic. The adventure yarn follows an expedition of treasure-seeking explorers in the Sahara Desert who unwittingly unleash a 3000-year-old mummy. Rachel Weisz, John Hannah, Arnold Vosloo.

programme.title: Keeping the Faith
programme.desc: Edward Norton and Ben Stiller are delightful in Norton's directorial debut about a priest and a rabbi who've been friends since childhood. But when another old pal (Jenna Elfman) reunites with the men, one of them is in danger of becoming a third wheel. Eli Wallach, Anne Bancroft, Ron Rifkin, Milos Forman.

programme.title: Barefoot
programme.desc: In this delightful, feel-good romance, a wealthy playboy falls for a sheltered beauty who charms his family at his brother's lavish wedding. Suddenly, the man whose life was going nowhere seems to have found the road to true happiness.

programme.title: Beverly Hills Cop
programme.desc: A crack Detroit detective pursues a pal's killer through the plastic jungle of Southern California, where he tweaks authority, tumbles with the bad guys and bends the rules.

programme.title: High Fidelity
programme.desc: John Cusack is in a groove as the owner of a Chicago used-record store in this smart 2000 romantic comedy. It's the story of a man who reflects on his messy love life while paying meticulous attention to all things vinyl. The charmer is based on the novel by Nick Hornby. Iben Hjejle, Jack Black, Todd Louiso, Joan Cusack, Tim Robbins, Lisa Bonet.

programme.title: The Crime of the Century
programme.desc: Part 1 of 2. A look at how Purdue Pharma worked with the FDA to get OxyContin approved for wider use, promoting the highly profitable pain medication's safety without sufficient evidence, and creating a campaign to redefine pain and how it's treated.

programme.title: Last Week Tonight With John Oliver
programme.sub-title: Last Week Tonight with John Oliver 220
programme.desc: Black hair discrimination; voting restriction bills; and the election recount in Arizona are discussed.

programme.title: Hacksaw Ridge
programme.desc: Riveting biopic about World War II Army medic Desmond Doss, a conscientious objector who refused to take a life or even carry a weapon. Doss was eventually awarded the Medal of Honor for saving the lives of 75 soldiers on the battlefields of Okinawa.

programme.title: Phantom Thread
programme.desc: In this stunning period drama set in 1950s London, a meticulous tailor for the rich and famous suddenly finds himself in love with a working-class woman. Their worlds collide as the tailor's obsession with her begins to disturb his professional life.

programme.title: Dream House
programme.desc: In this white-knuckle thriller, Will discovers that his family have been targeted by a deranged killer who massacred the people who previously lived in his house. With the help of a neighbor, he tries to solve the mystery of their deaths before it's too late.

programme.title: Live by Night
programme.desc: Joe Coughlin, the son of a Boston police lieutenant, moves to Florida to become a bootlegger in this sprawling crime epic set in the Prohibition era. As his operation grows, Coughlin faces off against local gangsters, Klansmen and religious evangelicals while he fights for control of Tampa's criminal underworld.

programme.title: The Debt
programme.desc: In this taut thriller, celebrated Mossad agent Rachel Singer must find out the truth when a man appears claiming to be the Nazi war criminal she supposedly killed 30 years earlier, during a mission that made her a legend.

programme.title: 10 Years
programme.desc: Adults attend their 10-year high-school reunion in this memorable drama as old flames are rekindled, a repentant bully regresses, rivals compete for the affections of a popular beauty and a musician longs for the crush who inspired his hit single.

programme.title: Henry Poole Is Here
programme.desc: Divine, Capra-esque comedy-drama starring Luke Wilson as a depressed man who moves into a run-down, suburban L.A. neighborhood hoping for some peace and quiet, but his well-meaning, religious neighbors think otherwise. When one of them spots the outline of a holy being on his stucco wall, his sanctuary turns into a blessed site to which people from miles around flock, looking for miracles. Radha Mitchell, Adriana Barraza, George Lopez, Cheryl Hines, Morgan Lily. Directed by Mark Pellington.

programme.title: Untamed Heart
programme.desc: An act of heroism kindles a romance between a lonely waitress and a sickly busboy.

programme.title: Miss Julie
programme.desc: Over the course of a midsummer night in Fermanagh in 1890, an unsettled daughter of the Anglo-Irish aristocracy encourages her father's valet to seduce her.

programme.title: Fine China
programme.desc: An average dinner at Lily's house turns tragic, leaving her alone in her grief, until she erupts in a song and dance that threatens everything her parents believe to be true.

programme.title: Unforgettable
programme.desc: In this riveting female-centric thriller, a jilted ex-wife grows jealous of her former husband's new bride, and decides to destroy the latter's reputation in an attempt to get her old life back.

programme.title: Unfaithful
programme.desc: \"Fatal Attraction\" director Adrian Lyne tackles infidelity once again with this involving erotic thriller. Oscar nominee Diane Lane and Richard Gere are superb as a happily married couple whose union is threatened when the wife begins an affair with an attractive book dealer (Olivier Martinez). Erik Per Sullivan, Myra Lucretia Taylor.

programme.title: Darkest Hour
programme.desc: This riveting historical drama depicts the early days of Winston Churchill's leadership of the U.K. during WWII, as he tries to rally the nation to action while many of his contemporaries advocate peace talks with Hitler.

programme.title: The Kingdom
programme.desc: An elite group of FBI agents clash with local authorities in Saudi Arabia while investigating a terrorist bombing of a Western housing compound. Jamie Foxx, Chris Cooper and Jennifer Garner star in this action-packed political thriller. Jason Bateman, Ashraf Barhom, Ali Suliman, Jeremy Piven. Directed by Peter Berg.

programme.title: The Crime of the Century
programme.desc: Conclusion. A spotlight on the mass marketing of the synthetic opioid fentanyl examines the connections between drug manufacturers and government policy. Video of sales retreats and promotional material reveals a deep cynicism among company employees and a disregard for the widespread, nefarious corporate practices.

programme.title: The Witches of Eastwick
programme.desc: Three female friends inadvertently bring the devil to their sleepy New England town. He proceeds to seduce each of them, and the trio must work together again to stop him from his plans for total domination.

programme.title: Stigmata
programme.desc: Patricia Arquette leaves her mark in a bloody, creepy chiller about a \"self-confessed atheist\" who \"exhibits the wounds of Christ.\" Gabriel Byrne is riveting as a Vatican priest, a debunker of miracles, sent to investigate the religious phenomenon. He arrives and in due course witnesses a couple of terrifying incidents that rock his faith.

programme.title: Nurse 3D (?)
programme.desc: In this bloody and intense horror film, a sexy nurse moonlights as a man-hating murderess until a younger coworker threatens to expose her.

programme.title: Lost Boys: The Tribe (?)
programme.desc: A vampire hunter is called in after a surfer and his sister tangle with a tribe of bloodsuckers. Corey Feldman reprises his signature role of Edgar Frog in this thrilling follow-up of the 1987 cult favorite. Tad Hilgenbrinck, Angus Sutherland, Autumn Reeser, Jamison Newlander, Corey Haim. Directed by P.J. Pesce.

programme.title: 8 Mile
programme.desc: Hard-hitting drama about a white rapper from inner-city Detroit whose talent for wordplay inspires dreams of a career in hip-hop. The original song \"Lose Yourself\" won an Oscar.

programme.title: Forces of Nature
programme.desc: Ben Affleck is an airplane passenger traveling to his wedding in Georgia and Sandra Bullock is the charmer seated next to him in this delightful romance. When their flight experiences trouble, they decide to find other modes of transportation. Fighting, flirting and hitching rides, they seem destined to be together---despite his impending nuptials.

programme.title: Keeping Up with the Steins
programme.desc: A Hollywood agent plans an extravagant bar mitzvah in Dodger Stadium to top a celebration thrown by his bitter rival. Jeremy Piven (\"Entourage\") stars in this warm and funny family comedy. Jami Gertz, Daryl Hannah, Garry Marshall, Doris Roberts, Daryl Sabara. Directed by Scott Marshall.

programme.title: Dinner for Schmucks
programme.desc: In this riotous comedy, Tim wants to snag a big promotion at work, but to do so he must take an eccentric nutcase to his boss's dinner party, where guests are supposed to bring the strangest person they can find.

programme.title: Broken City
programme.desc: In this nail-biting thriller, the mayor of NYC hires a disgraced former cop, now working as a private eye, to expose his wife's infidelities. As he does so, the PI begins to unravel a mystery that could bring about the end of more than just a marriage.

programme.title: The Grifters
programme.desc: A trio of con artists become tangled in a dangerous power struggle when Roy Dillon's mother and girlfriend compete for his affection.

programme.title: Crash
programme.desc: After a near-fatal car accident, a man (James Spader) and his wife are increasingly drawn to the connection between sex and death. They join an exclusive club of car-crash fetishists, who gather regularly to stage re-enactments of celebrity auto wrecks. Holly Hunter, Elias Koteas, Deborah Kara Unger.

programme.title: Surrogates
programme.desc: This dazzling, futuristic sci-fi thriller follows Greer, an FBI agent investigating a murder in a world where people no longer go outside but instead live life through robotic surrogates controlled from their homes. As Greer amasses clues, he uncovers a conspiracy involving the people responsible for creating the surrogates.

programme.title: Vice
programme.desc: Prepare for serious thrills as a cop pursues a female android that escaped from a hedonistic resort where people live out their wildest fantasies. Meanwhile, the owner of the resort dispatches a band of mercenaries to eliminate the android first.

programme.title: Hitman (?)
programme.desc: A genetically engineered assassin known as Agent 47 finds himself on the run with a hooker after he is double-crossed on a mission in Russia. Timothy Olyphant and Dougray Scott star in the explosive unrated adaptation of the popular video game. Olga Kurylenko, Robert Knepper, Ulrich Thomsen. Directed by Xavier Gens.

programme.title: The Score
programme.desc: Marlon Brando, Robert De Niro and Edward Norton team up in this tense caper about the daring heist of a priceless artifact of European royalty, but bickering among the principals threatens to precipitate a coup before the theft gets under way. Frank Oz directed. Angela Bassett, Gary Farmer, Jamie Harrold, Paul Soles.

programme.title: Rush
programme.desc: A female rookie cop is paired with an undercover officer trying to infiltrate a drug kingpin's organization. He is forced to partake of illegal substances as part of his cover, and he's become a junkie. She follows him down this self-destructive path after they become lovers.

programme.title: Lost Boys: The Thirst
programme.desc: When an ambitious alpha bloodsucker disguises vampire blood as a designer drug in a bid to claim the entire planet in the name of the undead, it's up to Edgar and Alan Frog to fight for the future of the entire human race.

programme.title: Twelve Monkeys (?)
programme.desc: A time traveler from 2035 goes back to 1996 to investigate how a deadly virus will spread around the world.

programme.title: Pi
programme.desc: In this award-winning intellectual thriller, a math genius (Sean Gullette) develops a dangerous obsession with an elusive 216-number sequence. He is pursued by corporate agents who are also after the number, which is tied to the stock market. Mark Margolis, Ben Shenkman. Written and directed by Darren Aronofsky.

programme.title: Executive Decision
programme.desc: Kurt Russell stars in this action-packed thriller about a terrorism expert whose team tries to rescue a hijacked plane carrying nerve gas. Steven Seagal, Halle Berry, John Leguizamo, Oliver Platt, Joe Morton. Stuart Baird (\"U.S. Marshals\") directed.

programme.title: Chasing Mavericks
programme.desc: In this inspiring sports drama, a young surfing prodigy enlists the help of an old pro in order to conquer a truly epic wave, and eventually the two surfers forge a bond of friendship that changes their lives.

programme.title: The Diving Bell and the Butterfly
programme.desc: Visually splendid and enthralling fact-based account of the travails and triumphs of a French magazine editor (Mathieu Amalric) who suffers a massive stroke at 43, leaving him with movement only in his left eyelid. Directed by Julian Schnabel, who was nominated for an Oscar, as was Ronald Harwood for his script, which was based on protagonist Jean-Dominique Bauby's best-selling 1997 memoir.

programme.title: The Running Man
programme.desc: A cop in 2019 America is framed for massacring rioting civilians during a famine. After escaping from jail he tries to prove his innocence, but is captured along with an innocent civilian, and they are forced to participate in a violent game show called \"The Running Man.\".

programme.title: A Walk Among the Tombstones
programme.desc: The thrills never stop when a NYC heroin trafficker hires a haunted ex-cop to find the men who abducted and killed his wife. But as the sleuth gets closer to his targets, he realizes that they're much more sinister than he could have imagined.

programme.title: The Kitchen
programme.desc: When their mobster husbands are sent to prison by the FBI, three New York housewives decide to continue their husbands' business on their own, soon becoming the most powerful mobsters in 1970s Hell's Kitchen.

programme.title: Showtime
programme.desc: A TV network blackmails the LAPD into letting them follow two cops for a reality TV show in this action-packed buddy comedy. The cops are a no-nonsense detective and an aspiring actor, and they're in pursuit of a ruthless arms dealer. Life begins to imitate art as the contentious duo are encouraged to make things more exciting for their audience.

programme.title: Her Smell
programme.desc: A fading '90s punk rocker struggles with life after the past success of her all-female grunge band. Now playing smaller venues and competing against her own sobriety and the pressures of motherhood, she takes a hiatus from the stage, to find herself and her sober creativity.

programme.title: Bridget Jones: The Edge of Reason
programme.desc: Renée Zellweger, Colin Firth and Hugh Grant return for this must-see sequel. Charming but insecure Bridget has finally landed the reserved Mr. Darcy (Firth), but she is concerned that their relationship won't last. Adding to her worries is the fact that her new employers have paired her with her womanizing ex-boyfriend, Daniel Cleaver (Grant).

programme.title: Good Boys
programme.desc: One day, 12-year-old Max gets invited by the cool kids to a kissing party. Panicked because he doesn't know how to kiss, he enlists the help of two of his friends, Thor and Lucas, to help him uncover the mystery of kissing. After online research proves to be unproductive, they decide to take the drone owned by Max's father in order to spy on the neighboring teens. When the drone unexpectedly crashes, the boys are thrust into an adventure.

programme.title: The Way Back
programme.desc: An alcoholic who has endured family tragedy works to redeem himself by coaching his high school alma mater's basketball team. But as he's brought back to his glory days as a promising athlete, he's forced to confront the demons that derailed him earlier in life.

programme.title: John Q
programme.desc: Riveting thriller about a family man whose son needs a lifesaving heart-transplant operation. When his health-care plan doesn't cover the boy's medical procedure, he takes drastic steps to rectify the situation.

programme.title: Walk the Line
programme.desc: Joaquin Phoenix and Reese Witherspoon give award-winning performances and do their own singing in this touching portrait of music legend Johnny Cash and his tumultuous love affair with June Carter. Ginnifer Goodwin, Robert Patrick, Dallas Roberts. Directed by James Mangold.

programme.title: Birth of the Dragon
programme.desc: In 1964 San Francisco, a pre-fame Bruce Lee challenges a Shaolin monk named Wong Jack Man to a fight behind closed doors. This engaging drama depicts this real-life event, which helped cement Lee's reputation as a legendary martial artist.

programme.title: Exodus
programme.desc: A chronicle of the plight of Jews-in-exile at the end of WWII, and activists' efforts to situate a vast number of Jews in Palestine for the purpose of influencing the U.N. vote to establish an Israeli state.

programme.title: Sound of My Voice
programme.desc: Novice filmmakers go through a rigorous training program in order to infiltrate and document a cult, and confront its mysterious leader, who claims to be on a mission from the future.

programme.title: Birthday Girl
programme.desc: In this scintillating comedy-drama, sparks fly between a lonely English bank teller (Ben Chaplin) and his Russian mail-order bride (Nicole Kidman). At first, he's upset that she doesn't speak English, but soon he discovers that she has other talents. He also learns she has arrived with two mysterious cousins in tow. Vincent Cassel, Mathieu Kassovitz.

programme.title: Bounce
programme.desc: Ben Affleck and Gwyneth Paltrow costar in this unusual drama. Affleck plays Buddy, an exec who gives another man his plane ticket as a favor. Minutes after takeoff, the plane crashes. Feeling responsible, Buddy tries to help the man's widow (Paltrow) by entering into a business relationship with her.

programme.title: Six Days, Seven Nights
programme.desc: In this romantic comedy, Anne Heche plays an ambitious magazine editor who becomes marooned on a deserted island with a gruff cargo pilot (Harrison Ford). Despite their conflicting personalities, the two castaways gradually fall for one another, even as they are besieged by mother nature and ruthless modern-day pirates. David Schwimmer, Jacqueline Obradors, Temuerra Morrison, Allison Janney.

programme.title: Season of the Witch
programme.desc: In this hair-raising supernatural thriller, medieval crusader Behmen (Nicolas Cage) and his men are ordered to capture a suspected witch and bring her back to an abbey after church officials accuse her of bringing about the Black Plague.

programme.title: Lady in the Water
programme.desc: In this mesmerizing horror fantasy, an apartment manager finds a sea nymph called a \"narf\" in the complex's swimming pool, and tries to return her to her natural habitat. However, otherworldly monsters are out to stop him.

programme.title: The Cell 2
programme.desc: A psychic investigator attempts to stop a sadistic serial killer who repeatedly brings his helpless victims back to life over and over again until they beg to die. Tessie Santiago stars in this terrifying sequel to the 2000 cult horror movie. Chris Bruno, Frank Whaley, Bart Johnson. Directed by Tim Iacofano.

programme.title: Killerman
programme.desc: Moe Diamond is a money launderer who mainly works around Manhattan's hectic jewelry circuit. After scoring a lucrative gig, he, together with his partner, Skunk, decides to make a quick one-off drug deal. Unfortunately for them, the cops catch wind of the trade and a chase ensues. Their car crashes, and the next thing Moe knows, he is in the hospital with amnesia. After Skunk gets him out, he has to expertly navigate an unfamiliar world in order to survive.

programme.title: The Nest
programme.desc: Successful businessman Rory (Jude Law) experiences a series of career highs until an unexpected twist in the market forces him to make alternative arrangements in his life. Rory then uproots his family and relocates from the United States to a remote country manor in England. However, the family's isolation begins to take a toll on their psyches, spurring a chain reaction of unsettling circumstances. Written and directed by Sean Durkin; co-starring Carrie Coon and Charlie Shotwell.

programme.title: Ziwe
programme.desc: Ziwe discusses the phenomenon of white women with interview guest Fran Lebowitz and hosts a focus group for real women named 'Karen'.

programme.title: City on a Hill
programme.desc: Jackie assumes the involvement of the Campbell brothers at the Copeland territory shootout and confronts Grace, who can no longer sidestep her sons' criminal activity, and is forced to make a terrible compromise. Resenting the outcome of a negotiation that he could not take part in, Decourcy finds comfort in the strength of Siobhan, who keeps her head even after tragedy strikes. Jenny insists on helping Maeve, whether or not that means defying Jackie.

programme.title: The Exorcist
programme.desc: When a young girl begins acting strangely, her mother seeks out a priest, who is convinced the child is possessed by a demon.

programme.title: Rosemary's Baby
programme.desc: A young woman living in an old New York City apartment building becomes pregnant following a horrible nightmare, and begins to fear the worst for her unborn child while suspecting that she is surrounded by evil.

programme.title: Grizzly II: Revenge
programme.desc: A ferocious grizzly bear seeks revenge after a poacher kills her cub.

programme.title: Waves
programme.desc: A suburban African-American family living in South Florida cope with life, love, and unexpected calamity. Their ambitions for happiness and success are thwarted by a career-ending sports injury and the traumatic aftermath of an unintended murder.

programme.title: The Taking of Pelham 1 2 3
programme.desc: Denzel Washington stars as a New York City subway dispatcher who draws on his extensive knowledge of the transportation system to thwart a dangerous criminal mastermind in this explosive action thriller. Walter Garber is drifting through his daily routine when he receives word that a heavily armed gang has hijacked a crowded subway train. Led by cunning thief Ryder, the gunmen will begin executing everyone aboard should the authorities fail to deliver a sizable ransom in just one hour.

programme.title: The Reluctant Fundamentalist
programme.desc: In this riveting drama, a Princeton-educated Wall Street analyst from Pakistan reveals how 9/11 changed his worldview and opinion of the U.S. during a conversation with an American journalist investigating the abduction of a foreign professor in Lahore.

programme.title: City on a Hill
programme.desc: An assistant U.S. attorney overdoses and ends up left for dead, but Decourcy Ward suspects Jackie Rohr's involvement. Jackie, in turn, goes after the BPD for a questionable drug arrest at Braxton Summit, a federal housing project. Community activist Grace Campbell recruits Siobhan Quays to work on behalf of Braxton and its residents, but their efforts are subverted as tensions flare between rival gangs.

programme.desc: Decourcy increases pressure on the Justice Department, but Jackie counters by looking into his adversary's romantic past. While Jackie's digging up dirt, Siobhan is planning ahead, focused on starting a family even as Decourcy remains preoccupied by the escalating conflict. Jenny realizes she can't keep ignoring her mother after an unsettling phone call. With business at the salon all but dead, Cathy Ryan turns to an unlikely income source.

programme.title: City on a Hill
programme.sub-title: Is the Total Black, Being Spoken
programme.desc: Jackie uncovers one of Decourcy's informants and hatches a plan to use him as a pawn to discredit the assistant district attorney. Decourcy stops by the Rohr house, hoping to get something out of Jenny that he can use against her husband. Siobhan receives some welcome news, in the midst of plotting her run for City Council. And her client, Kelvin Campbell, is released from custody, though he can't free himself of what happened on Valentine's Day.

programme.title: City on a Hill
programme.desc: After seeing Holly in the ICU, Jackie reckons with the destructive consequences of his actions, as Rickey Townsend prepares to testify against Decourcy. With violence intensifying between the Copeland Crew and the Braxton Boys, Decourcy, Anton and Siobhan face off in the interrogation room. Grace, left reflecting on her role as a mother and leader in the community, makes an unfortunate miscalculation. And back at the Rohr house, Jenny makes fast friends with the mysterious woman from Belfast.

programme.title: City on a Hill
programme.desc: U.S. Attorney Karen Shimizu tries to get rid of her troublesome agent once and for all as Jackie schemes his way into a new mission. At the Suffolk County Courthouse, Decourcy and Siobhan spar on opposing sides of a legal battle. Meeting dead-ends at every turn in the effort to help her son, Grace does something desperate. With a nudge from Maeve, Jenny surprises Benny with some rebellious fun. On the other side of town, Cathy re-ups her supply by going straight to the source.

programme.title: City on a Hill
programme.desc: With Anton on the lam, Kelvin struggles to lead the Braxton Boys and Jackie homes in on Grace, whom he knows she's hiding something. Sidelined from the investigation, Decourcy finds himself at a disconnect with Siobhan, as he seeks vengeance and she focuses on recovery. When Cathy's arrangement with Isaac falls through, she pays a reluctant visit to old friends for help. Jenny, meanwhile, finally uncovers the truth about her new friend.

programme.title: City on a Hill
programme.desc: Jackie assumes the involvement of the Campbell brothers at the Copeland territory shootout and confronts Grace, who can no longer sidestep her sons' criminal activity, and is forced to make a terrible compromise. Resenting the outcome of a negotiation that he could not take part in, Decourcy finds comfort in the strength of Siobhan, who keeps her head even after tragedy strikes. Jenny insists on helping Maeve, whether or not that means defying Jackie.

programme.desc: Denzel Washington stars as a New York City subway dispatcher who draws on his extensive knowledge of the transportation system to thwart a dangerous criminal mastermind in this explosive action thriller. Walter Garber is drifting through his daily routine when he receives word that a heavily armed gang has hijacked a crowded subway train.
